        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48763",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend\\Controller is old MVC port from ZF1. Look the new Mvc component and Zend\\Mvc\\Router subnamespace for ZF2 beta1.\r\nSo priority major is wrong.\r\n\r\nHow do you want use ZF in app without have ZF in the include path?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-22T11:09:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-22T11:09:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48785",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hannes",
                        "name": "hannes",
                        "displayName": "Johannes Lichtenwallner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "sorry, setting major priority was an error.\r\n\r\n{quote}How do you want use ZF in app without have ZF in the include path?{quote}\r\n\r\nI thought thats the intention of _Zend\\Loader\\StandardAutoloader_ as the constructor contains:\r\n{code}\r\n$this->registerNamespace('Zend', dirname(__DIR__));\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hannes",
                        "name": "hannes",
                        "displayName": "Johannes Lichtenwallner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-25T14:04:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-25T14:04:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48786",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The question is: how do you get the standard autoloader in the first place? You have to have it either on your include_path or require it by a known path in the first place. :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-25T14:12:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-25T14:12:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48787",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hannes",
                        "name": "hannes",
                        "displayName": "Johannes Lichtenwallner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "yes, you're right, it doesn't really matter. But currently ZendFramework chooses, not the user.\r\n\r\n_Zend\\Application\\Application_ requires the StandardAutoloader by absolute path in his constructor:\r\n{code}\r\nrequire_once __DIR__ . '\/..\/Loader\/StandardAutoloader.php';\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nSo you just have to know the absolute path to Zend\\Application\\Application. Thats the way i prefer to use ZendFramwork or other libraries (e.g. Doctrine), because i use a shared library path for all projects\/services with following directory structure:\r\n{code}\r\n\/path\/to\/library\r\n\t\/dynamic\r\n\t\t\/Doctrine\r\n\t\t\t\/2.1.1\r\n\t\t\t\/2.1.2\r\n\t\t\/ZendFramework\r\n\t\t\t\/1.11.10\r\n\t\t\t\/1.11.11\r\n\t\t\t\/2.0.0beta1\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nFor ZF 1.x i have to use set_include_path, in 2.x not necessarily.\r\n\r\nBut as i said: it doesn't matter, so it doesn't bother me, if resolution will be _won't fix_ :-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hannes",
                        "name": "hannes",
                        "displayName": "Johannes Lichtenwallner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-25T14:35:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-25T14:35:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49698",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend\\Controller has been removed from the mainline ZF2 distribution in favor of a new MVC (Zend\\Mvc).  A module providing a ZF1-compatible MVC layer can be found in [modules\/ZendFramework1Mvc|https:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/zf2\/tree\/master\/modules\/ZendFramework1Mvc]",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-02-23T16:17:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-02-23T16:17:40.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
